{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883491923,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae78e09001ovwEirKm8YT1Gu","messageID":"msg_d7ae7762e001WUyR7EGehv8frm","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d79aaf6f57ed4873b9f5d38a93e6bbe4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n6: \n7: | Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n8: |--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n9: | `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n10: | `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n11: | `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n12: | `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── picod/\n23: │   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n24: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n25: ├── router/\n26: │   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n27: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n28: ├── workloadmanager/\n29: │   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n30: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n31: └── agentd/\n32: │   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n33: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Binary Dependency Graph\n37: \n38: ```\n39: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n41: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n42: │                                                                               │\n43: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n44: │   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n45: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n46: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n47: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n48: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n49: │   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n50: │   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n51: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n52: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n53: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n54: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n56: │   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n57: │   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n58: │   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n59: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: │                                                                               │\n61: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Deployment Model\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n69: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n70: │                                                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n72: │  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n73: │  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n74: │  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n75: │           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n76: │           │                      │                              │\n77: │           ▼                      ▼                              │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n79: │  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n80: │  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n81: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n82: │                                                                  │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n84: │  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n85: │  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n86: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n87: │                                                                  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: \n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n94: │  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n95: │  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n96: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: package main\n108: \n109: type CLIConfig struct {\n110:     LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n111:     MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n112:     HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### PicoD CLI Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package main\n120: \n121: type PicoDConfig struct {\n122:     CLIConfig\n123:     Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n124:     Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n125:     AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n126:     MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n127:     MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n128:     SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Router CLI Configuration\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package main\n136: \n137: type RouterConfig struct {\n138:     CLIConfig\n139:     Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n140:     MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n141:     Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n142:     EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n143:     TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n144:     TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n145:     StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n146:     StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n147:     StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package main\n155: \n156: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n157:     CLIConfig\n158:     Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n159:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n160:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n161:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n162:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n163:     GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n164:     GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n165:     Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n166:     MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Agentd CLI Configuration\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: package main\n174: \n175: type AgentdConfig struct {\n176:     CLIConfig\n177:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n178:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n179:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n180:     Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n181:     LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n182:     LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n183:     Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### Binary Entry Point Interface\n192: \n193: Each binary follows this pattern:\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: package main\n197: \n198: type Binary interface {\n199:     InitFlags() *Config\n200:     ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n201:     Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n202:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n203: }\n204: \n205: func main() {\n206:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n207:     flag.Parse()\n208:     \n209:     cfg := InitFlags()\n210:     if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n211:         klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214:     \n215:     ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n216:     defer cancel()\n217:     \n218:     if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n219:         klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n220:         os.Exit(1)\n221:     }\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Signal Handling Contract\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: package main\n229: \n230: func setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n231:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n232:     \n233:     c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n234:     signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n235:     \n236:     go func() {\n237:         sig := <-c\n238:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n239:         cancel()\n240:         \n241:         if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n242:             <-c\n243:             klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n244:             os.Exit(1)\n245:         }\n246:     }()\n247:     \n248:     return ctx\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Health Check Contract\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: package main\n256: \n257: type HealthChecker interface {\n258:     Live() bool\n259:     Ready() bool\n260: }\n261: \n262: func (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n263:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n264:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n265:         if h.Live() {\n266:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n267:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n268:         } else {\n269:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n270:         }\n271:     })\n272:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n273:         if h.Ready() {\n274:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n275:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n276:         } else {\n277:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n278:         }\n279:     })\n280:     return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n281: }\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### Flag Registration Contract\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: package main\n288: \n289: func InitFlags() *Config {\n290:     cfg := &Config{}\n291:     \n292:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n293:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n294:     \n295:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n296:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n297:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n298:     \n299:     flag.Parse()\n300:     \n301:     return cfg\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Binary Implementation Details\n308: \n309: ### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n310: \n311: **Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n312: \n313: **Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func main() {\n317:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n318:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n319: \n320:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n321:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n322:     flag.Parse()\n323: \n324:     config := &picod.Config{\n325:         Port:      *port,\n326:         Workspace: *workspace,\n327:     }\n328: \n329:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n330:     if err != nil {\n331:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n332:         os.Exit(1)\n333:     }\n334: \n335:     if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n336:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n337:         os.Exit(1)\n338:     }\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Endpoints**:\n343: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n344: |------|--------|---------|\n345: | `/health` | GET | Health check |\n346: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n347: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n348: | `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n349: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n350: \n351: ### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n352: \n353: **Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n354: \n355: **Implementation Template**:\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: func main() {\n359:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n360:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n361:     \n362:     cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n363:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n364:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n365:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n366:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n367:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n368:     flag.Parse()\n369:     \n370:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n371:     \n372:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n373:     if err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376:     \n377:     sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n378:     jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n379:     \n380:     server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n381:         Port:                 cfg.Port,\n382:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n383:         Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n384:     }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n385:     \n386:     if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n387:         klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n388:     }\n389: }\n390: ```\n391: \n392: **Endpoints**:\n393: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n394: |------|--------|---------|\n395: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n396: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n397: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n398: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n399: \n400: ### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n401: \n402: **Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n403: \n404: **Implementation Template**:\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: func main() {\n408:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n409:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n410:     \n411:     cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n412:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n413:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n414:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n415:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n416:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n417:     flag.Parse()\n418:     \n419:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n420:     \n421:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n422:     if err != nil {\n423:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n424:     }\n425:     \n426:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n432:         workloadmanager.Config{\n433:             Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n434:             ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n435:             WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n436:             ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n437:         },\n438:         klog.Logger{},\n439:         k8sClient,\n440:         store,\n441:     )\n442:     \n443:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n444:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n445:     \n446:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n447:     \n448:     errCh := server.Start()\n449:     select {\n450:     case err := <-errCh:\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n452:     case <-ctx.Done():\n453:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: **Endpoints**:\n459: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n460: |------|--------|---------|\n461: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n462: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n463: | `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n464: | `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n465: | `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n466: \n467: ### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n468: \n469: **Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n470: \n471: **Implementation Template**:\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func main() {\n475:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n476:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n477:     \n478:     cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n479:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n480:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n481:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n482:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n483:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n484:     flag.Parse()\n485:     \n486:     k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n487:     if err != nil {\n488:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n489:     }\n490:     \n491:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n492:         LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n493:         LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n494:         LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n495:     })\n496:     if err != nil {\n497:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n498:     }\n499:     \n500:     if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n501:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n505:     if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n506:         klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n507:     }\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Categories\n516: \n517: | Category | Description | Action |\n518: |----------|-------------|--------|\n519: | `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n520: | `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n521: | `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n522: | `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n523: | `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n524: | `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n525: \n526: ### Error Handling Pattern\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: func handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n530:     if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n531:         klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n532:         return\n533:     }\n534:     \n535:     if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n536:         klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n541:     os.Exit(1)\n542: }\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n546: \n547: ```\n548: 1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n549: 2. Cancel main context\n550: 3. Stop accepting new requests\n551: 4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n552: 5. Close store connections\n553: 6. Close K8s client connections\n554: 7. Exit with code 0\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ### Validation Errors\n558: \n559: ```go\n560: func ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n561:     if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n562:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n563:     }\n564:     \n565:     if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n566:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n567:     }\n568:     \n569:     if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n570:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n571:     }\n572:     \n573:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n574:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     return nil\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Testing Strategy\n584: \n585: ### Unit Tests\n586: \n587: #### Flag Parsing Tests\n588: \n589: ```go\n590: func TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n591:     tests := []struct {\n592:         name     string\n593:         args     []string\n594:         expected *Config\n595:     }{\n596:         {\n597:             name: \"default values\",\n598:             args: []string{},\n599:             expected: &Config{\n600:                 Port:           8080,\n601:                 LogLevel:       \"info\",\n602:                 IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n603:             },\n604:         },\n605:         {\n606:             name: \"custom port\",\n607:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n608:             expected: &Config{\n609:                 Port:          9000,\n610:             },\n611:         },\n612:         {\n613:             name: \"multiple flags\",\n614:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n615:             expected: &Config{\n616:                 Port:  9000,\n617:                 Debug: true,\n618:             },\n619:         },\n620:     }\n621:     \n622:     for _, tt := range tests {\n623:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n624:             fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n625:             cfg := &Config{}\n626:             setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n627:             \n628:             err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n629:             require.NoError(t, err)\n630:             \n631:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n632:         })\n633:     }\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: #### Signal Handler Tests\n638: \n639: ```go\n640: func TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n641:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n642:     \n643:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n644:     \n645:     select {\n646:     case <-ctx.Done():\n647:         assert.True(t, true)\n648:     case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n649:         t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n650:     }\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: #### Config Validation Tests\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n658:     tests := []struct {\n659:         name        string\n660:         config      *Config\n661:         expectError bool\n662:     }{\n663:         {\n664:             name: \"valid config\",\n665:             config: &Config{\n666:                 Port:          8080,\n667:                 IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n668:             },\n669:             expectError: false,\n670:         },\n671:         {\n672:             name: \"invalid port\",\n673:             config: &Config{\n674:                 Port: -1,\n675:             },\n676:             expectError: true,\n677:         },\n678:         {\n679:             name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n680:             config: &Config{\n681:                 IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n682:             },\n683:             expectError: true,\n684:         },\n685:     }\n686:     \n687:     for _, tt := range tests {\n688:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n689:             err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n690:             if tt.expectError {\n691:                 assert.Error(t, err)\n692:             } else {\n693:                 assert.NoError(t, err)\n694:             }\n695:         })\n696:     }\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### Integration Tests\n701: \n702: #### Binary Startup Tests\n703: \n704: ```go\n705: func TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n706:     if testing.Short() {\n707:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n708:     }\n709:     \n710:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n711:     \n712:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n713:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n714:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n715:     \n716:     err := cmd.Start()\n717:     require.NoError(t, err)\n718:     \n719:     defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n720:     \n721:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n722:         resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n723:         if err != nil {\n724:             return false\n725:         }\n726:         defer resp.Body.Close()\n727:         return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n728:     }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: #### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n733: \n734: ```go\n735: func TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n736:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n737:     \n738:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n739:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n740:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n741:     \n742:     err := cmd.Start()\n743:     require.NoError(t, err)\n744:     \n745:     waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n746:     \n747:     syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n748:     \n749:     done := make(chan error, 1)\n750:     go func() {\n751:         done <- cmd.Wait()\n752:     }()\n753:     \n754:     select {\n755:     case err := <-done:\n756:         assert.NoError(t, err)\n757:     case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n758:         t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n759:     }\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ### Build Tests\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: func TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n767:     binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n768:     \n769:     for _, binary := range binaries {\n770:         t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n771:             cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n772:             output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n773:             assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n774:             \n775:             assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n776:         })\n777:     }\n778: }\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Metrics\n784: \n785: ### Prometheus Metrics\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: var (\n789:     startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n790:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n792:             Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n793:         },\n794:         []string{\"binary\"},\n795:     )\n796:     \n797:     shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n798:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n799:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n800:             Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n801:         },\n802:         []string{\"binary\"},\n803:     )\n804:     \n805:     configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n806:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n807:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n808:             Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n809:         },\n810:         []string{\"binary\"},\n811:     )\n812: )\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ---\n816: \n817: ## Configuration\n818: \n819: ### Environment Variables\n820: \n821: | Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n822: |----------|--------|---------|\n823: | `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n824: | `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n825: | `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n826: | `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n827: | `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n828: | `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n829: \n830: ### Command-Line Flags Summary\n831: \n832: | Flag | Default | Purpose |\n833: |------|---------|---------|\n834: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n835: | `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n836: | `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n837: | `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n838: | `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n839: | `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n840: | `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n841: | `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Build Configuration\n846: \n847: ### Go Module\n848: \n849: ```go\n850: // go.mod\n851: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n852: \n853: go 1.24\n854: \n855: require (\n856:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n857:     github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n858:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n859:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n860: )\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ### Makefile Targets\n864: \n865: ```makefile\n866: .PHONY: build clean\n867: \n868: build:\n869: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n870: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n871: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n872: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n873: \n874: clean:\n875: \trm -rf bin/\n876: \n877: build-picod:\n878: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n879: \n880: build-router:\n881: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n882: \n883: build-workloadmanager:\n884: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n885: \n886: build-agentd:\n887: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ### Docker Build\n891: \n892: ```dockerfile\n893: # Dockerfile for picod\n894: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n895: WORKDIR /app\n896: COPY . .\n897: RUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n898: \n899: FROM alpine:3.19\n900: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n901: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n902: ```\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Implementation Checklist\n907: \n908: - [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n909: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n910: - [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n911: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n912: - [ ] Common signal handling package\n913: - [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n914: - [ ] Health check server integration\n915: - [ ] Metrics server integration\n916: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n917: - [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n918: - [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n919: - [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n920: - [ ] Makefile build targets\n921: - [ ] Docker build configurations\n922: - [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n923: \n924: ---\n925: \n926: ## Dependencies\n927: \n928: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n929: |---------|---------|---------|\n930: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n931: | `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n932: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n933: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n934: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n935: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 935 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775883491875,"end":1775883491920}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883491940,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae795fb001flLC2yW3vj3WhS","messageID":"msg_d7ae7762e001WUyR7EGehv8frm","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c9cba4a9627c4a3ead033c5a8cf3b6c4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module and dependencies\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|--------|\n7: | Go module | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n8: | Go version (go.mod) | `1.24.4` |\n9: | Toolchain | `go1.24.9` |\n10: \n11: **Direct `require` (from go.mod):**  \n12: `github.com/agiledragon/gomonkey/v2 v2.13.0`, `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.35.0`, `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2`, `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0`, `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.17.1`, `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1`, `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.69`, `golang.org/x/net v0.47.0`, `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1`, `k8s.io/utils v0.0.0-20251002143259-bc988d571ff4`, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.1.1`, `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2`\n13: \n14: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n15: \n16: ### groupversion_info.go — package and scheme\n17: \n18: ```go\n19: // +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n20: package v1alpha1\n21: \n22: var (\n23:     GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n24:     SchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n25:     AddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n26: )\n27: ```\n28: \n29: ### register.go — kind metadata\n30: \n31: ```go\n32: var (\n33:     CodeInterpreterKind             = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n34:     CodeInterpreterGroupKind        = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n35:     CodeInterpreterListKind         = \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n36:     CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n37: )\n38: \n39: var (\n40:     AgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n41:     AgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n42:     AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n43: )\n44: \n45: var SchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n46: \n47: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n48:     return GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n49: }\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ### agent_type.go — AgentRuntime types\n53: \n54: ```go\n55: // +genclient\n56: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n57: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n58: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n59: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n60: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n61: type AgentRuntime struct {\n62:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n63:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n64:     Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n65:     Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n70:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n71:     Template *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n72:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n73:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n74:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n75:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n76:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n77:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n78: }\n79: \n80: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n81:     // +optional\n82:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n83: }\n84: \n85: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n86:     // +optional\n87:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,rep,name=labels\"`\n88:     // +optional\n89:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,rep,name=annotations\"`\n90:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n91:     Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=spec\"`\n92: }\n93: \n94: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n95: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n96: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n97:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n98:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n99:     Items           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### codeinterpreter_types.go — CodeInterpreter and shared types\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: // +genclient\n107: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n108: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n109: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n110: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n111: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n112: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n113:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n114:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n115:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n116:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n117: }\n118: \n119: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n120:     // +optional\n121:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n122:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n123:     Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`\n124:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n125:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`\n126:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n127:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"`\n128:     // +optional\n129:     WarmPoolSize *int32 `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n130:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"picod\"\n131:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=picod;none\n132:     // +optional\n133:     AuthMode AuthModeType `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`\n134: }\n135: \n136: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n137:     // +optional\n138:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n139:     // +optional\n140:     Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n141: }\n142: \n143: type CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n144:     // +optional\n145:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n146:     // +optional\n147:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n148:     // +optional\n149:     RuntimeClassName *string `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n150:     Image string `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n151:     // +optional\n152:     ImagePullPolicy corev1.PullPolicy `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n153:     // +optional\n154:     // +patchMergeKey=name\n155:     // +patchStrategy=merge\n156:     // +listType=map\n157:     // +listMapKey=name\n158:     ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n159:     // +optional\n160:     Environment []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n161:     // +optional\n162:     // +listType=atomic\n163:     Command []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n164:     // +optional\n165:     Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n166:     // +optional\n167:     Resources corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n168: }\n169: \n170: type TargetPort struct {\n171:     // +optional\n172:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n173:     // +optional\n174:     Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n175:     Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n176:     // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n177:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;\n178:     Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n179: }\n180: \n181: type AuthModeType string\n182: \n183: const (\n184:     AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n185:     AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n186: )\n187: \n188: type ProtocolType string\n189: \n190: const (\n191:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n192:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n193: )\n194: \n195: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n196: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n197: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n198:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n199:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n200:     Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n201: }\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n205: \n206: ```go\n207: const (\n208:     AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n209:     CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n210:     SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n211:     SandboxClaimsKind   = \"SandboxClaim\"\n212: )\n213: \n214: type SandboxInfo struct {\n215:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n216:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n217:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n218:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n219:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n220:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n221:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n222:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n223:     Status string `json:\"status\"`\n224: }\n225: \n226: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n227:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n228:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n229:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n230: }\n231: \n232: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n233:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n234:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n235:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n236: }\n237: \n238: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n239:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n240:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n241:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n242:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n243: }\n244: \n245: func (car *CreateSandboxRequest) Validate() error\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: const (\n252:     resourceGroup               = \"agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n253:     sessionResourceName         = \"sessions\"\n254:     agentRuntimeResourceName    = \"agentruntimes\"\n255:     codeInterpreterResourceName = \"codeinterpreters\"\n256: )\n257: \n258: var (\n259:     ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound    = errors.New(\"agent runtime not found\")\n260:     ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = errors.New(\"code interpreter not found\")\n261:     ErrTemplateMissing         = errors.New(\"resource has no pod template\")\n262:     ErrPublicKeyMissing        = errors.New(\"public key not yet loaded from Router Secret\")\n263: )\n264: \n265: func NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID string) error\n266: func NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind string) error\n267: func NewUpstreamUnavailableError(err error) error\n268: func NewInternalError(err error) error\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n272: \n273: ### Config and Server\n274: \n275: ```go\n276: type Config struct {\n277:     Port             string\n278:     RuntimeClassName string\n279:     EnableTLS        bool\n280:     TLSCert          string\n281:     TLSKey           string\n282:     EnableAuth       bool\n283: }\n284: \n285: type Server struct {\n286:     config            *Config\n287:     router            *gin.Engine\n288:     httpServer        *http.Server\n289:     k8sClient         *K8sClient\n290:     sandboxController *SandboxReconciler\n291:     tokenCache        *TokenCache\n292:     informers         *Informers\n293:     storeClient       store.Store\n294:     wg                sync.WaitGroup\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### HTTP routes\n299: \n300: | Method | Path | Auth middleware | Handler |\n301: |--------|------|-----------------|---------|\n302: | GET | `/health` | No | `handleHealth` |\n303: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` |\n304: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n305: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n306: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | If `EnableAuth` | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n307: \n308: ### ErrorResponse\n309: \n310: ```go\n311: type ErrorResponse struct {\n312:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n313: }\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ### K8sClient and defaults\n317: \n318: ```go\n319: const (\n320:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n321:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n322: )\n323: \n324: var (\n325:     SessionIdLabelKey         = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n326:     WorkloadNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n327:     SandboxNameLabelKey       = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n328:     LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\n329:     IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n330: )\n331: \n332: type K8sClient struct {\n333:     clientset       *kubernetes.Clientset\n334:     dynamicClient   dynamic.Interface\n335:     scheme          *runtime.Scheme\n336:     baseConfig      *rest.Config\n337:     clientCache     *ClientCache\n338:     dynamicInformer dynamicinformer.DynamicSharedInformerFactory\n339:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n340:     podInformer     cache.SharedIndexInformer\n341:     podLister       listersv1.PodLister\n342: }\n343: ```\n344: \n345: - REST config: `QPS = 50`, `Burst = 100`; in-cluster config else kubeconfig loading rules.\n346: - `NewClientCache(100)` for user dynamic clients.\n347: \n348: ### GVR variables (`informers.go`)\n349: \n350: ```go\n351: var (\n352:     AgentRuntimeGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n353:         Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\",\n354:     }\n355:     CodeInterpreterGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n356:         Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\",\n357:     }\n358:     SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n359:         Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n360:     }\n361:     SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n362:         Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n363:     }\n364: )\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ### Identity secret (workload_builder.go)\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: const (\n371:     IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n372:     PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n373: )\n374: \n375: var IdentitySecretNamespace = \"default\" // overridden by env AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Sandbox reconciler\n379: \n380: ```go\n381: type SandboxReconciler struct {\n382:     client.Client\n383:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n384:     watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n385:     mu       sync.RWMutex\n386: }\n387: \n388: type SandboxStatusUpdate struct {\n389:     Sandbox *sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox\n390: }\n391: ```\n392: \n393: - `Reconcile`: when `getSandboxStatus(sandbox) == \"running\"`, notify waiter channel (buffer 1), non-blocking send with `default` branch warning on full channel.\n394: - `getSandboxStatus`: returns `\"running\"` if a condition has `Type == string(sandboxv1alpha1.SandboxConditionReady)` and `Status == metav1.ConditionTrue`, else `\"unknown\"`.\n395: \n396: ### Garbage collector\n397: \n398: ```go\n399: const gcOnceTimeout = 2 * time.Minute\n400: \n401: type garbageCollector struct {\n402:     k8sClient   *K8sClient\n403:     interval    time.Duration\n404:     storeClient store.Store\n405: }\n406: ```\n407: \n408: - `newGarbageCollector(k8s, store, 15*time.Second)` — **GC interval: 15s**.\n409: - Per tick: `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout), 16)` — **batch size 16**.\n410: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), 16)` — **batch size 16**.\n411: - Single tick context timeout: **2 minutes**.\n412: \n413: ### Token cache\n414: \n415: - `NewTokenCache(1000, 5*time.Minute)` — max entries **1000**, TTL **5m** per entry (LRU + last-access expiry).\n416: \n417: ### Auth context keys\n418: \n419: ```go\n420: type contextKey string\n421: \n422: const (\n423:     contextKeyUserToken          contextKey = \"userToken\"\n424:     contextKeyServiceAccount     contextKey = \"serviceAccount\"\n425:     contextKeyServiceAccountName contextKey = \"serviceAccountName\"\n426:     contextKeyNamespace          contextKey = \"namespace\"\n427: )\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ### CLI flags (`cmd/workload-manager/main.go`)\n431: \n432: | Flag | Default | Meaning |\n433: |------|---------|---------|\n434: | `-port` | `8080` | API port |\n435: | `-runtime-class-name` | `kuasar-vmm` | Stored on `Config.RuntimeClassName` (flag parsed in `main`; **not read** elsewhere in `pkg/workloadmanager` in current source) |\n436: | `-enable-tls` | `false` | TLS |\n437: | `-tls-cert` | `\"\"` | Cert path |\n438: | `-tls-key` | `\"\"` | Key path |\n439: | `-enable-auth` | `false` | TokenReview auth |\n440: \n441: - Controller-runtime manager: metrics bind `0`, health probe `0`.\n442: - Shutdown: HTTP shutdown timeout **15s**, then cancel ctx, `WaitForBackgroundWorkers`, `CloseStore`.\n443: \n444: ### Store dependency\n445: \n446: ```go\n447: // github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\n448: type Store interface {\n449:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n450:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n451:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n452:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n453:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n454:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n455:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n456:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n457:     Close() error\n458: }\n459: ```\n460: \n461: Server uses `store.Storage()` singleton.\n462: \n463: ### Sandbox build notes\n464: \n465: - AgentRuntime: sandbox name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`, UUID session ID, ports from `spec.Ports`, TTL/idle from `MaxSessionDuration` / `SessionTimeout` when non-nil.\n466: - CodeInterpreter: default ports if empty: single `TargetPort{Port:8080, Protocol:ProtocolTypeHTTP, PathPrefix:\"/\"}`; if `WarmPoolSize > 0`: creates `SandboxClaim` + minimal `Sandbox` metadata only, `sandboxEntry.Kind = SandboxClaimsKind`; else builds full `Sandbox` with container `code-interpreter` and optional `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode == picod`.\n467: - `buildSandboxObject`: APIVersion `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind `Sandbox`, labels include `managed-by: agentcube-workload-manager`, annotation `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey` = idle duration string, lifecycle `ShutdownTime` = now+TTL, `Replicas: ptr.To[int32](1)`.\n468: \n469: ### Pod name annotation\n470: \n471: - Read from created sandbox: key from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/controllers`.`SandboxPodNameAnnotation` (comment in source documents value `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`).\n472: \n473: ## CodeInterpreter controller (supplementary)\n474: \n475: - Reconciles `CodeInterpreter`; when `WarmPoolSize > 0` ensures `SandboxTemplate` (name = CI name) and `SandboxWarmPool` (name = CI name, replicas = WarmPoolSize, templateRef name = CI name); injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` in template unless `AuthModeNone`; requeues 5s if public key not cached and auth not none.\n\n(End of file - total 475 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration — Design\n\n## Module and dependencies\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|--------|\n| Go module | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Go version (go.mod) | `1.24.4` |\n| Toolchain | `go1.24.9` |\n\n**Direct `require` (from go.mod):**  \n`github.com/agiledragon/gomonkey/v2 v2.13.0`, `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.35.0`, `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.2`, `github.com/google/uuid v1.6.0`, `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.17.1`, `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.11.1`, `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.69`, `golang.org/x/net v0.47.0`, `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1`, `k8s.io/utils v0.0.0-20251002143259-bc988d571ff4`, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.1.1`, `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2`\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n### groupversion_info.go — package and scheme\n\n```go\n// +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\npackage v1alpha1","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md","time":{"start":1775883491881,"end":1775883491938}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883491942,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae79222001j7SmlJWhI5EWIG","messageID":"msg_d7ae7762e001WUyR7EGehv8frm","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0510085293614e3d97d005511d11ba7b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `co