{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883504980,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae7c5b4001OB4Ao97kyTlGiq","messageID":"msg_d7ae79ac7001NkT69EslrH9pnu","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6d6664ec41884070a3db92d61b3a859c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-024 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Encapsulate Docker SDK operations into a well-structured `DockerService` class that provides a clean abstraction layer for container image lifecycle management (build, push, remove). This service acts as the foundation for CLI `build` and `publish` commands, enabling:\n17: \n18: 1. **Docker Availability Check**: Verify Docker daemon connectivity before operations\n19: 2. **Image Building**: Build container images from Dockerfile with proxy support\n20: 3. **Image Information Retrieval**: Get metadata (ID, size) for built images\n21: 4. **Image Pushing**: Push images to registries with authentication support\n22: 5. **Image Removal**: Clean up local images after operations\n23: \n24: **Current State**: Basic `DockerService` exists with core methods (`build_image`, `push_image`, `remove_image`, `get_image_info`, `check_docker_available`), but lacks proper SDK-based helper methods (`_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk`) and has incomplete `_get_image_info` implementation. The class uses inline Docker client calls instead of proper encapsulation.\n25: \n26: **Target State**: \n27: - Complete `DockerService` with all methods per design specification\n28: - Add `_docker_login_sdk()` for SDK-based registry authentication\n29: - Add `_tag_image_sdk()` for SDK-based image tagging\n30: - Add `_get_image_info()` as internal implementation detail\n31: - Consistent error handling with verbose logging\n32: - Full unit test coverage with mocked Docker SDK\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n37: \n38: ### 2.1 In Scope\n39: \n40: | Deliverable | Description |\n41: |-------------|-------------|\n42: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Complete `DockerService` class with all public and private methods |\n43: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | Unit tests for all `DockerService` methods |\n44: \n45: ### 2.2 DockerService Methods\n46: \n47: | Method | Purpose | Status |\n48: |--------|---------|--------|\n49: | `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose flag | Existing |\n50: | `check_docker_available()` | Ping Docker daemon to verify availability | Existing |\n51: | `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)` | Build image from Dockerfile, return image metadata | Existing |\n52: | `get_image_info(image_name)` | Get image ID and size for a given image | Existing |\n53: | `_get_image_info(image_name)` | Internal implementation for image info retrieval | To Add |\n54: | `_format_size(size_bytes)` | Convert bytes to human-readable size string | Existing |\n55: | `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)` | Push image to registry with optional auth | Existing |\n56: | `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` | SDK-based Docker registry login | To Add |\n57: | `_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)` | SDK-based image tagging for push | To Add |\n58: | `remove_image(image_name)` | Remove local image, return success boolean | Existing |\n59: \n60: ### 2.3 Out of Scope\n61: \n62: | Item | Reason |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Docker daemon installation/setup | Assumes Docker is already installed on the host |\n65: | Container runtime operations | Only image lifecycle, not container execution |\n66: | Multi-platform image builds | Not specified in requirements; `docker buildx` would be separate feature |\n67: | Docker Compose integration | Different paradigm; CLI uses `build` + `publish` workflow |\n68: | Cloud provider Docker APIs | Cloud build mode is handled by `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` |\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n73: \n74: ### 3.1 新增文件\n75: \n76: No new files; modifications to existing files:\n77: \n78: ```\n79: cmd/cli/\n80: ├ agentcube/\n81: │   └── services/\n82: │       └── docker_service.py       # MODIFY: Add _docker_login_sdk, _tag_image_sdk, _get_image_info\n83: └── tests/\n84:     └── test_docker_service.py      # MODIFY: Add tests for new methods\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n88: \n89: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n90: |------------|---------|--------|\n91: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; `docker.from_env()` for client initialization |\n92: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | `AgentMetadata` type in `build_image_legacy` |\n93: | Standard library `time` | N/A | Build/push timing measurement |\n94: \n95: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n96: \n97: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n98: |----------|--------------|\n99: | `BuildRuntime._build_local` | `check_docker_available()`, `build_image()`, `get_image_info()` |\n100: | `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image` | `push_image()`, `_docker_login_sdk()`, `_tag_image_sdk()` |\n101: | `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing` | `push_image()` |\n102: | `tests/test_build_runtime.py` | Mock `DockerService` methods |\n103: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Mock `DockerService` methods |\n104: \n105: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n106: \n107: - **No breaking changes**: All public method signatures remain unchanged\n108: - **New private methods**: `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk`, `_get_image_info` are internal; no API impact\n109: - **Behavioral change**: `push_image` may now use `_tag_image_sdk` for explicit tagging before push\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n114: \n115: ### Alternative 1: subprocess-based Docker CLI\n116: \n117: **Approach**: Use `subprocess.run()` to execute `docker build`, `docker push`, `docker tag` commands.\n118: \n119: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n120: |--------|------------|\n121: | Pros | No SDK dependency; familiar CLI commands; easier debugging |\n122: | Cons | Platform-specific path handling; harder error parsing; no structured output; no streaming logs via SDK |\n123: \n124: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK (`docker.from_env()`) provides structured API responses, proper error types, and consistent behavior across platforms.\n125: \n126: ### Alternative 2: Docker API REST client\n127: \n128: **Approach**: Use `httpx` to call Docker Engine REST API directly (`/build`, `/images/push`).\n129: \n130: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n131: |--------|------------|\n132: | Pros | No SDK dependency; flexible request handling |\n133: | Cons | Requires Docker socket access; complex auth header handling; less robust than SDK |\n134: \n135: **Decision**: Rejected. Docker SDK already handles socket communication, TLS, and authentication correctly.\n136: \n137: ### Alternative 3: Separate ImageService and RegistryService\n138: \n139: **Approach**: Split Docker operations into `ImageService` (build, remove) and `RegistryService` (login, push, tag).\n140: \n141: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n142: |--------|------------|\n143: | Pros | Smaller classes; clearer separation |\n144: | Cons | More complexity; image lifecycle is cohesive; spec defines single `DockerService` |\n145: \n146: **Decision**: Rejected. All Docker operations are cohesive for CLI workflow; single class matches design specification.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 5. Risks\n151: \n152: | Risk | Mitigation |\n153: |------|------------|\n154: | Docker daemon not running | `check_docker_available()` ping before operations; fail fast with `RuntimeError` |\n155: | Registry authentication failure | `_docker_login_sdk()` catches exceptions; verbose logging |\n156: | Image tag mismatch | `_tag_image_sdk()` validates source/target; logs on failure |\n157: | Build timeout | No explicit timeout in SDK; CLI level timeout in `BuildRuntime` |\n158: | Large image sizes | `_format_size()` handles GB ranges; no truncation |\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n163: \n164: - [ ] Add `_docker_login_sdk(self, registry, username, password)` method\n165: - [ ] Add `_tag_image_sdk(self, source_image, target_image)` method\n166: - [ ] Add `_get_image_info(self, image_name)` private implementation\n167: - [ ] Update `push_image` to use `_docker_login_sdk` and `_tag_image_sdk` when registry_url provided\n168: - [ ] Add unit tests for `_docker_login_sdk` with mock client\n169: - [ ] Add unit tests for `_tag_image_sdk` with mock client\n170: - [ ] Add unit tests for `_get_image_info` edge cases\n171: - [ ] Verify existing tests still pass\n172: - [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_docker_service.py` to validate\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 7. References\n177: \n178: - Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Docker integration (lines 135-151)\n179: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — DockerService class signature\n180: - AR-021 — CLI build command (uses DockerService)\n181: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses DockerService)\n182: - Docker SDK for Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 182 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-024 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEncapsulate Docker SDK operations into a well-structured `DockerService` class that provides a clean abstraction layer for container image lifecycle management (build, push, remove). This service acts as the foundation for CLI `build` and `publish` commands, enabling:\n\n1. **Docker Availability Check**: Verify Docker daemon connectivity before operations\n2. **Image Building**: Build container images from Dockerfile with proxy support\n3. **Image Information Retrieval**: Get metadata (ID, size) for built images","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883504965,"end":1775883504979}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883504982,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae7c94c001ufbUckutkD11k5","messageID":"msg_d7ae79ac7001NkT69EslrH9pnu","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-440028cc62a74d1783d60a2672ac0f29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-025 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n17: \n18: 1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n19: 2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n20: 3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)\n21: 4. **CLI Option Mapping**: Map Typer CLI options to metadata updates via `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n22: \n23: **Current State**: No dedicated metadata service or data models exist. CLI commands directly handle YAML files without schema validation, leading to inconsistent metadata handling and potential configuration errors.\n24: \n25: **Target State**: \n26: - `MetadataService` class with load/save/update/validate methods\n27: - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 20+ fields and validators\n28: - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI-to-metadata option mapping\n29: - Consistent error handling for invalid metadata files\n30: - Unit test coverage for validation scenarios\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n35: \n36: ### 2.1 In Scope\n37: \n38: | Deliverable | Description |\n39: |-------------|-------------|\n40: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class for metadata lifecycle management |\n41: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI options |\n42: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n43: | `tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Unit tests for MetadataService |\n44: | `tests/test_agent_metadata.py` | Unit tests for AgentMetadata validators |\n45: \n46: ### 2.2 MetadataService Methods\n47: \n48: | Method | Purpose |\n49: |--------|---------|\n50: | `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose logging flag |\n51: | `load_metadata(workspace_path)` | Load `AgentMetadata` from YAML with fallback filenames |\n52: | `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` | Persist metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n53: | `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` | Apply partial updates and return new metadata |\n54: | `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` | Validate workspace directory and file structure |\n55: | `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for *.py files in Python workspace |\n56: | `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for pom.xml in Java workspace |\n57: \n58: ### 2.3 AgentMetadata Model Fields\n59: \n60: | Field | Type | Default | Validation |\n61: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n62: | `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Unique agent identifier |\n63: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n64: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Validator: `['python', 'java']` lowercase |\n65: | `entrypoint` | `str` | Required | Command to launch agent |\n66: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Validator: `1..65535` |\n67: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Validator: `['local', 'cloud']` lowercase |\n68: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n69: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version for publishing |\n70: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image info |\n71: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication config |\n72: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n73: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for publishing |\n74: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n75: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n76: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n77: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n78: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n79: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Readiness probe path |\n80: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Readiness probe port |\n81: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n82: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session ID for agent |\n83: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment info |\n84: \n85: ### 2.4 MetadataOptions Fields\n86: \n87: | Field | Type | Default |\n88: |-------|------|---------|\n89: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n90: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n91: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n92: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n93: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n94: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n95: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n96: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n97: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n98: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n99: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n100: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n101: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n102: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n103: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n104: \n105: ### 2.5 Out of Scope\n106: \n107: | Item | Reason |\n108: |------|--------|\n109: | Database-backed metadata storage | YAML file storage per spec; database would be separate feature |\n110: | Metadata encryption/secrets | Security handled by separate secret management (future) |\n111: | Multi-agent metadata aggregation | Single agent per workspace per spec |\n112: | Version history tracking | Git handles versioning; metadata file is single state |\n113: | Cloud metadata sync | Metadata is local file; cloud sync would be separate feature |\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n118: \n119: ### 3.1 新增文件\n120: \n121: ```\n122: cmd/cli/\n123: ├── agentcube/\n124: │   ├── models/\n125: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # NEW: models package marker\n126: │   │   └── pack_models.py        # NEW: MetadataOptions dataclass\n127: │   ├── services/\n128: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # MODIFY: export MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n129: │   │   └── metadata_service.py   # NEW: MetadataService class\n130: │   └── runtime/\n131: │   │   └── pack_runtime.py       # MODIFY: use MetadataService\n132: │   └── cli/\n133: │       └── main.py               # MODIFY: use MetadataOptions for pack command\n134: └── tests/\n135:     ├── test_metadata_service.py  # NEW: MetadataService unit tests\n136:     └── test_agent_metadata.py    # NEW: AgentMetadata validator tests\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n140: \n141: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n142: |------------|---------|--------|\n143: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | BaseModel for AgentMetadata; validators for field constraints |\n144: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for metadata file persistence |\n145: | `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling for workspace validation |\n146: | Standard library `logging` | stdlib | Verbose logging support |\n147: \n148: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n149: \n150: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n151: |----------|--------------|\n152: | `PackRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()` |\n153: | `BuildRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for version increment |\n154: | `PublishRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for deployment info |\n155: | `InvokeRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for endpoint retrieval |\n156: | `StatusRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for status display |\n157: | CLI `pack` command | `MetadataOptions.from_options()` for CLI option mapping |\n158: \n159: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n160: \n161: - **Metadata file name**: Primary filename is `agent_metadata.yaml`; fallbacks are `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n162: - **Schema validation**: Existing metadata files must conform to new validators; invalid language/build_mode will raise errors\n163: - **Required fields**: `agent_name` and `entrypoint` are now required; existing files missing these will fail validation\n164: - **Port validation**: Port must be 1-65535; values outside range will be rejected\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n169: \n170: ### Alternative 1: dataclasses instead of Pydantic\n171: \n172: **Approach**: Use Python `dataclasses` for `AgentMetadata` with manual validation methods.\n173: \n174: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n175: |--------|------------|\n176: | Pros | No external dependency; simpler for basic data structures |\n177: | Cons | No automatic validation; more boilerplate; no serialization helpers; no type coercion |\n178: \n179: **Decision**: Rejected. Pydantic provides automatic validation, type coercion, and `model_dump()` for serialization without boilerplate.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: JSON-based metadata storage\n182: \n183: **Approach**: Store metadata as JSON instead of YAML.\n184: \n185: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n186: |--------|------------|\n187: | Pros | Native Python `json` module; no pyyaml dependency; easier machine parsing |\n188: | Cons | Less human-readable; no comments support; spec explicitly requires YAML |\n189: \n190: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires YAML format (`agent_metadata.yaml`) for human-readable configuration with comments.\n191: \n192: ### Alternative 3: Single metadata file in home directory\n193: \n194: **Approach**: Store all agent metadata in a central file (e.g., `~/.agentcube/metadata.yaml`) instead of workspace-local files.\n195: \n196: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n197: |--------|------------|\n198: | Pros | Centralized management; easier multi-agent overview |\n199: | Cons | Workspace independence lost; harder to version control; spec requires per-workspace file |\n200: \n201: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` for workspace-local configuration and Git version control.\n202: \n203: ### Alternative 4: Configuration file inheritance/templating\n204: \n205: **Approach**: Support base metadata file with inheritance (e.g., `extends: base-metadata.yaml`).\n206: \n207: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n208: |--------|------------|\n209: | Pros | Reuse common settings; reduce duplication |\n210: | Cons | Adds complexity; not in spec; inheritance resolution overhead |\n211: \n212: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as enhancement if users request configuration reuse patterns.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 5. Risks\n217: \n218: | Risk | Mitigation |\n219: |------|------------|\n220: | Invalid YAML syntax | `yaml.safe_load` raises `YAMLDecodeError`; catch and re-raise with context |\n221: | Missing required fields | Pydantic `ValidationError` with field-specific messages |\n222: | Unknown fields in YAML | Pydantic `extra=\"ignore\"` (or forbid per spec requirement) |\n223: | Workspace validation race condition | Check file existence before validation; handle `FileNotFoundError` |\n224: | Language mismatch | `_validate_python_workspace` / `_validate_java_workspace` with clear error messages |\n225: | Port range violation | Pydantic validator `validate_port` raises `ValueError` with valid range |\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n230: \n231: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/__init__.py` package marker\n232: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n233: - [ ] Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options(options: Dict[str, Any])` factory method\n234: - [ ] Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n235: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n236: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` with fallback filenames\n237: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` with YAML options\n238: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` partial update\n239: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` structure check\n240: - [ ] Implement `_validate_python_workspace` for *.py file check\n241: - [ ] Implement `_validate_java_workspace` for pom.xml check\n242: - [ ] Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all fields\n243: - [ ] Implement `validate_language` validator (python/java lowercase)\n244: - [ ] Implement `validate_build_mode` validator (local/cloud lowercase)\n245: - [ ] Implement `validate_port` validator (1-65535 range)\n246: - [ ] Update `agentcube/services/__init__.py` exports\n247: - [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n248: - [ ] Add unit tests for metadata load/save with valid YAML\n249: - [ ] Add unit tests for fallback filename behavior\n250: - [ ] Add unit tests for Pydantic validators\n251: - [ ] Add unit tests for workspace validation scenarios\n252: - [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py` to validate\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## 7. References\n257: \n258: - Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Metadata file format, Workspace validation\n259: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — MetadataService, AgentMetadata, MetadataOptions signatures\n260: - AR-021 — CLI pack command (uses MetadataService for pack flow)\n261: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses metadata for deployment info)\n262: - Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n263: - PyYAML Documentation: https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation\n\n(End of file - total 263 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-025 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n\n1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883504968,"end":1775883504981}}}}
