{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883585575,"sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae907ef001p0uvzEv1mHUkqu","messageID":"msg_d7ae7cd87001lDbXe4slnvYI0j","sessionID":"ses_28518f257ffe9qEgrj715STgqt","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-2793e8541604415b9b11e747506117e6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","content":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-030 |\n| Module | manifests |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components. The Helm Chart enables:\n\n1. **One-command Deployment**: Install AgentCube stack with `helm install agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n2. **Configuration Flexibility**: Customize deployment via `values.yaml` (image registry, replicas, resources, Redis settings)\n3. **Environment Adaptability**: Support dev/staging/prod environments through values overrides\n4. **Component Isolation**: Deploy router, workloadmanager, agentd, Redis independently via subcharts or enabled flags\n\n**Components to be templated**:\n\n| Component | Kind | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| `workloadmanager` | Deployment + Service | Workload manager HTTP server (port 8080) |\n| `router` | Deployment + Service | Session routing reverse proxy (port 8080) |\n| `agentd` | Deployment | Idle cleanup controller with leader election |\n| `redis` | Deployment + Service | Session store (Redis 7 or Valkey) |\n| RBAC | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding | Router and WorkloadManager permissions |\n| Secrets | Secret | JWT signing key, identity secret for picod auth |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (name, version, appVersion, dependencies) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default values for all components |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-service.yaml` | WorkloadManager Service template (port 8080) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-deployment.yaml` | Router Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-service.yaml` | Router Service template (port 8080) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-rbac.yaml` | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding for router |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentd-deployment.yaml` | Agentd Deployment template with leader election |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-deployment.yaml` | Redis/Valkey Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-service.yaml` | Redis Service template (port 6379) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/jwt-secret.yaml` | JWT signing key Secret template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/identity-secret.yaml` | Picod-Router identity Secret template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Template helpers (name, labels, image helpers) |\n\n### 2.2 Values Schema\n\n| Section | Key | Default | Description |\n|---------|-----|---------|-------------|\n| `global` | `imageRegistry` | `\"\"` | Global image registry override |\n| `global` | `imagePullSecrets` | `[]` | Global image pull secrets |\n| `workloadmanager` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable WorkloadManager deployment |\n| `workloadmanager.image` | `repository` | `workloadmanager` | Image repository |\n| `workloadmanager.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n| `workloadmanager.image` | `pullPolicy` | `IfNotPresent` | Image pull policy |\n| `workloadmanager` | `replicas` | `1` | Deployment replicas |\n| `workloadmanager` | `resources` | `{}` | Resource requests/limits |\n| `workloadmanager` | `env` | `[]` | Extra environment variables |\n| `workloadmanager.service` | `type` | `ClusterIP` | Service type |\n| `workloadmanager.service` | `port` | `8080` | Service port |\n| `router` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Router deployment |\n| `router.image` | `repository` | `agentcube-router` | Image repository |\n| `router.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n| `router` | `replicas` | `1` | Deployment replicas |\n| `router` | `maxConcurrent` | `1000` | Max concurrent requests |\n| `router.rbac` | `create` | `true` | Create RBAC resources |\n| `router.serviceAccountName` | `agentcube-router` | ServiceAccount name |\n| `router.service` | `type` | `ClusterIP` | Service type |\n| `router.service` | `port` | `8080` | Service port |\n| `agentd` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Agentd deployment |\n| `agentd.image` | `repository` | `agentd` | Image repository |\n| `agentd.image` | `tag` | `latest` | Image tag |\n| `agentd` | `idleThreshold` | `30m` | Idle cleanup threshold |\n| `agentd` | `checkInterval` | `5m` | Cleanup check interval |\n| `agentd` | `leaderElection` | `true` | Enable leader election |\n| `agentd` | `leaderElectionID` | `agentcube-agentd` | Leader election ID |\n| `redis` | `enabled` | `true` | Enable Redis deployment |\n| `redis.image` | `repository` | `redis` | Image repository (redis or valkey) |\n| `redis.image` | `tag` | `7-alpine` | Image tag |\n| `redis` | `passwordRequired` | `false` | Require Redis password |\n| `redis` | `password` | `\"\"` | Redis password (empty = no auth) |\n| `redis.service` | `port` | `6379` | Redis service port |\n| `jwt` | `secretName` | `agentcube-jwt-key` | JWT secret name |\n| `jwt` | `keyNamespace` | `agentcube` | Namespace for JWT secret |\n\n### 2.3 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| CRD installation | CRDs installed separately via agent-sandbox release assets |\n| Sandbox Pod templates | Dynamic creation by WorkloadManager, not static Helm template |\n| HorizontalPodAutoscaler | Not in initial scope; scale via replicas value |\n| Ingress resources | Network ingress handled separately per environment |\n| PersistentVolumeClaims | Redis uses ephemeral storage by default; PVC optional |\n| NetworkPolicies | Environment-specific; not in base chart |\n| Prometheus ServiceMonitor | Monitoring stack installed separately |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Helm Chart metadata file |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` | WorkloadManager Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-service.yaml` | WorkloadManager Service template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-deployment.yaml` | Router Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-service.yaml` | Router Service template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-rbac.yaml` | Router RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentd-deployment.yaml` | Agentd Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-deployment.yaml` | Redis Deployment template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-service.yaml` | Redis Service template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/jwt-secret.yaml` | JWT signing key Secret template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/identity-secret.yaml` | Picod-Router identity Secret template |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Named template helpers |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| N/A | No modifications required (pure addition) |\n\n### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `Helm 3` | Template rendering and release management |\n| `Kubernetes 1.24+` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC resources |\n| `agent-sandbox CRDs` | Required for WorkloadManager sandbox operations |\n| `docker images` | Pre-built images for router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod |\n\n### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base` with values overrides |\n| `GitHub Actions (e2e.yml)` | E2E test workflow uses Helm chart for Kind cluster deployment |\n| `Production deployments` | `helm install` with environment-specific values files |\n| `CI/CD pipeline` | `build-push-release.yml` pushes images referenced by chart values |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Static Kubernetes manifests (no Helm)\n\n**Approach**: Provide static YAML files in `manifests/` directory without templating.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No Helm dependency; simpler for single-environment deployment |\n| Cons | No parameterization; requires manual edits per environment; no release management; no rollback support |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Helm provides essential parameterization, release tracking, and rollback capabilities for production deployments.\n\n### Alternative 2: Kustomize overlays\n\n**Approach**: Use Kustomize with base manifests and environment overlays.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Native kubectl support; declarative overlays; GitOps-friendly |\n| Cons | No release history; no rollback; no hook support; requires multiple overlay directories |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Helm provides better release management and is already used in E2E tests (`run_e2e.sh`). Kustomize could be added later for GitOps workflows.\n\n### Alternative 3: Operator pattern for all components\n\n**Approach**: Deploy all components via a custom Kubernetes Operator.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Full lifecycle management; reconciliation; CRD-based configuration |\n| Cons | High complexity; longer development time; agentd already uses controller-runtime pattern |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. Agentd uses controller-runtime; other components are simpler HTTP servers. Operator pattern adds unnecessary complexity for Deployment/Service management.\n\n### Alternative 4: Multiple separate charts (one per component)\n\n**Approach**: Create independent Helm charts for each component (router-chart, workloadmanager-chart, agentd-chart, redis-chart).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Independent versioning; selective deployment; clear ownership |\n| Cons | Complex dependency management; more release coordination; shared helpers duplicated |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube components are tightly integrated; single chart with `enabled` flags provides cleaner deployment experience. Subchart structure could be added later if needed.\n\n### Alternative 5: Include CRDs in Helm chart\n\n**Approach**: Bundle agent-sandbox CRDs in Helm chart `crds/` directory.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | One-command full installation; no separate CRD step |\n| Cons | CRDs from external project (agent-sandbox); version mismatch risk; E2E uses separate download |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. CRDs come from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` releases. Keeping CRDs separate aligns with E2E workflow (`kubectl apply` from GitHub releases). Chart focuses on AgentCube-specific deployments.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Image registry mismatch | `global.imageRegistry` value allows registry override; defaults work for local Kind |\n| RBAC permission scope too broad | ClusterRole grants minimal permissions (Pod, Secret, TokenReview, CRD access); namespace-scoped option in values |\n| Redis password exposure | Default `passwordRequired=false`; production should set password via Secret reference |\n| Leader election deadlock | Agentd uses controller-runtime leader election with proper timeouts; single replica default avoids split-brain |\n| Helm template syntax errors | `_helpers.tpl` tested via `helm template` command; E2E validates rendered manifests |\n| Missing namespace | `--create-namespace` in E2E; explicit namespace in values for production |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with metadata\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with default configuration\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` with named templates\n- [ ] Implement `workloadmanager-deployment.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `workloadmanager-service.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `router-deployment.yaml` template with Redis address env\n- [ ] Implement `router-service.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `router-rbac.yaml` with ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] Implement `agentd-deployment.yaml` template with leader election\n- [ ] Implement `redis-deployment.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `redis-service.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `jwt-secret.yaml` template\n- [ ] Implement `identity-secret.yaml` template\n- [ ] Add `enabled` conditionals for each component template\n- [ ] Add resource limits/requests templates\n- [ ] Add liveness/readiness probe templates\n- [ ] Validate chart with `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n- [ ] Test template rendering with `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n- [ ] Update E2E script to use new chart structure if needed\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage (`manifests/charts/base` path, values examples)\n- design.md — Deployment model (Router, WorkloadManager, Agentd architecture)\n- sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Component configuration (flags, defaults)\n- Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values\n- Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC resource schemas\n- `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` — CRD requirements for WorkloadManager"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883585539,"end":1775883585572}}}}
